-- Embratel, Petrobras, Volcan Cia., Soquimich: Latin America Equity Preview
-- B y   N a t h a n   G i l l
-- 2010-09-27T03:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/embratel-petrobras-soquimich-latin-america-equity-preview.html
The following companies may have
unusual price changes today in Latin American trading. Stock
symbols are in parentheses and share prices reflect the previous
close.  The  MSCI Latin America Index  rose 0.3 percent to 4,251.38.
In Brazil, preferred shares usually are the most-traded class of
stock.  Brazil  Embratel Participacoes SA  (EBTP4 BZ): The
telecommunications company controlled by Mexican billionaire
Carlos Slim approved a 3.5-billion-real local bond issue,
according to a regulatory filing. The shares gained 0.1 percent
to 10.57 reais.  Petroleo Brasileiro SA  (PETR4 BZ): The state-controlled oil
company said the government’s sovereign wealth fund bought 386
million shares in the company’s $70 billion offering, equal to
about 2.9 percent of the company’s total outstanding capital,
including shares to be issued in a supplementary over-allotment,
Petrobras said in a regulatory filing. The shares slumped 1.9
percent to 26.3 reais.  Chile  Soc. Quimica y Minera de Chile SA  (SQM/B CC): Chile’s
largest fertilizer producer may rise to 26,000 pesos by the end
of 2011, Chilean brokerage firm BICE Inversiones said, citing
growth in all of Soquimich’s business segments due to higher
fertilizer demand, an expansion of production capacity and an
expected increase in potash prices. The shares rose 0.2 percent
to 23,511 pesos.  Peru  Volcan Cia. Minera SAA  (VOLCABC1 PE): The country’s exports
rose 33 percent to $21.6 billion in the first eight months of
the year as metal prices increased, Comexperu said in an e-
mailed statement. Mineral exports accounted for 60 percent of
overseas sales through August, the group said. Peru’s largest
zinc producer climbed 1.8 percent to 3.46 soles.  To contact the reporters on this story:
